[According to BBC (thanks to Mary Marshall <mjm2020@googlemail.com> for submitting the article), "The 11 countries and territories were later identified by the WHO as Armenia, Sweden, Moldova, North Macedonia, Azerbaijan, Kazakhstan, Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Kyrgyzstan, Ukraine, and Kosovo." These are areas we have flagged in the Worldometer section of our posts as places to keep an eye on. Basically, the Balkan States and the Newly Independent States seem to be heavily represented in this group. - Mod.MPP

